<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:src="http://nwalsh.com/xmlns/litprog/fragment" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.0" xml:id="author.othername.in.middle">
<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>author.othername.in.middle</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo role="type">boolean</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>
<refnamediv>
<refname>author.othername.in.middle</refname>
<refpurpose>Is <tag>othername</tag> in <sgmltag>author</sgmltag> a
middle name?</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<src:fragment xml:id="author.othername.in.middle.frag">
<xsl:param name="author.othername.in.middle" select="1"/>
</src:fragment>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>

<para>If true (non-zero), the <tag>othername</tag> of an <sgmltag>author</sgmltag>
appears between the <tag>firstname</tag> and
<tag>surname</tag>.  Otherwise, <sgmltag>othername</sgmltag>
is suppressed.
</para>

</refsect1>
</refentry>
